f items\", \"Professional network\" | Card-based feed | **LinkedIn** |\n82: | \"Dashboard\", \"Analytics\", \"Admin panel\" | Clean minimal dashboard | **Stripe**, **Linear** |\n83: | \"Stories\", \"Timeline\", \"Posts\" | Social feed | **Instagram**, **Twitter** |\n84: | \"Drag and drop\", \"Kanban board\" | Task management | **Trello**, **Asana** |\n85: | \"Chat\", \"Messaging\" | Messaging UI | **Slack**, **Discord** |\n86: | \"Calendar\", \"Scheduling\" | Calendar UI | **Google Calendar**, **Calendly** |\n87: | \"E-commerce\", \"Products\", \"Cart\" | Shopping UI | **Amazon**, **Shopify** |\n88: \n89: ### 2.3 Create Design Pillars\n90: \n91: **Based on key features, create 3-4 design pillars:**\n92: \n93: **Template:**\n94: ```\n95: **Design Philosophy:**\n96: \n97: **Core Inspiration (Must Study):**\n98: 1. **[Reference App 1]** - [Key feature to study]\n99: 2. **[Reference App 2]** - [Key feature to study]\n100: 3. **[Reference App 3]** - [Key feature to study]\n101: 4. **[Reference App 4]** - [Key feature to study]\n102: \n103: **The [Number] Pillars:**\n104: - [Feature Area 1] = [Reference App] ([specific pattern])\n105: - [Feature Area 2] = [Reference App] ([specific pattern])\n106: - [Feature Area 3] = [Reference App] ([specific pattern])\n107: ```\n108: \n109: **Example:**\n110: ```\n111: **Core Inspiration (Must Study):**\n112: 1. **Product Hunt** - Upvote buttons, card layout, ranking\n113: 2. **Reddit** - Comment threading, nested replies\n114: 3. **LinkedIn** - Professional feed, achievement feel\n115: 4. **Stripe** - Clean dashboard, minimal design\n116: \n117: **The Three Pillars:**\n118: - Feed = LinkedIn (professional cards, achievement vibes)\n119: - Comments = Reddit (threaded, vertical lines, indentation)\n120: - Dashboard = Stripe (clean, content-first, one action per page)\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## PHASE 2.5: DOMAIN & REFERENCE RESEARCH (MANDATORY)\n126: \n127: > **This step MUST be performed before generating the Design Guide.**\n128: > **Purpose:** Research the top products in the relevant domain to automatically identify standard UI patterns and essential sections.\n129: > **Instead of hardcoding a checklist**, discover \"what should naturally exist in this domain\" through research.\n130: \n131: ### 2.5.1 Competitor / Similar Product Research\n132: \n133: Perform WebSearch based on the industry and core features extracted from the PRD:\n134: \n135: ```\n136: Search queries:\n137:   1. \"[industry] best [product type] UI design 2025\" (e.g., \"design feedback SaaS best UI 2025\")\n138:   2. \"[competitor1] landing page\" (competitors specified in PRD)\n139:   3. \"[competitor2] dashboard UI\"\n140:   4. \"best [industry] web app design examples\"\n141: ```\n142: \n143: Research targets: Landing pages, dashboards, and core feature screens of the **top 3-5 products**.\n144: \n145: ### 2.5.2 Derive Standard Patterns by Page Type\n146: \n147: Extract **\"elements present in 80%+ of top products\"** from research results:\n148: \n149: | Page Type | Research Perspective |\n150: |-----------|---------------------|\n151: | Landing | What sections exist? (Hero, Features, How it Works, Pricing, Testimonials, Social Proof, CTA, Footer, etc.) |\n152: | Dashboard | What UI elements exist? (Search, Notifications, KPIs, Activity Feed, Tables, Quick Actions, etc.) |\n153: | Detail/Editor | What tools/panels exist? (Toolbar, Filters, Canvas/Content, Side Panel, Status Bar, etc.) |\n154: | Auth | What flows exist? (Social Login, Form Layout, Error States, Redirect, etc.) |\n155: | Settings | What sections exist? (Profile, Billing, Team, Notifications, Danger Zone, etc.) |\n156: \n157: ### 2.5.3 Deep Dive into PRD-Specified References\n158: \n159: If the PRD contains specific UI references (e.g., \"Notion-style Org Switcher\"), research the **actual latest UI patterns** of that product:\n160: \n161: ```\n162: Example:\n163:   PRD says: \"Notion-style Org Switcher\"\n164:   → WebSearch: \"Notion workspace switcher UI 2025\"\n165:   → Findings: icon + org name + dropdown arrow, \"+ New Workspace\" at bottom, search feature\n166:   → Reflect in the Org Switcher brief in the Design Guide\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ### 2.5.4 Save Research Results\n170: \n171: Save to `.claude-project/design/{PROJECT}_DomainResearch.md`:\n172: \n173: ```markdown\n174: # Domain Research — [PROJECT_NAME]\n175: \n176: ## Industry: [Industry]\n177: ## Competitors Analyzed: [Product1], [Product2], [Product3]\n178: \n179: ## Landing Page — Standard Sections\n180: (List of common sections discovered from research)\n181: \n182: ## Dashboard — Standard Elements\n183: (Common UI elements discovered from research)\n184: \n185: ## [Core Feature Screen] — Standard Patterns\n186: (Common patterns discovered from research)\n187: \n188: ## PRD Reference Analysis\n189: | PRD Reference | Actual UI Pattern | Notes |\n190: |--------------|-------------------|-------|\n191: ```\n192: \n193: This file is **injected as context** during Design Guide generation and HTML generation, ensuring domain standards are followed without omissions.\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ## PHASE 3: CREATE DESIGN SYSTEM\n198: \n199: ### 3.1 Color Palette\n200: \n201: **From PRD, extract:**\n202: \n203: | PRD Field | Design System Color | Default if Not Specified |\n204: |-----------|-------------------|-------------------------|\n205: | \"Preferred Main Color\" | Primary Color | #0066FF (Blue - trust) |\n206: | Success states | Success Color | #10B981 (Green) |\n207: | Warning states | Warning Color | #F59E0B (Orange/Yellow) |\n208: | Error states | Error Color | #EF4444 (Red) |\n209: | N/A | Background | #F9FAFB (Light Gray) |\n210: | N/A | Surface (Cards) | #FFFFFF (White) |\n211: | N/A | Text Primary | #1E293B (Dark Gray) |\n212: | N/A | Text Secondary | #64748B (Medium Gray) |\n213: | N/A | Border | #E5E7EB (Light Gray) |\n214: \n215: **Additional Context Colors:**\n216: \n217: Look at PRD features for color usage hints:\n218: - \"Original ideas badge\" → Success color\n219: - \"Similar ideas warning\" → Warning color\n220: - \"Duplicate ideas\" → Error color\n221: - Status indicators → Map to success/warning/error\n222: \n223: **Template:**\n224: ```\n225: ### Colors\n226: - Primary [Color Name]: [HEX] ([Usage from PRD])\n227: - Success [Color]: [HEX] ([Usage from PRD])\n228: - Warning [Color]: [HEX] ([Usage from PRD])\n229: - Error/Danger [Color]: [HEX] ([Usage from PRD])\n230: - Grays: 50-900 scale (standard)\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### 3.2 Typography\n234: \n235: **From PRD, extract:**\n236: \n237: | PRD Field | Design System Value | Default if Not Specified |\n238: |-----------|-------------------|-------------------------|\n239: | \"Preferred Font\" | Font Family | Inter, SF Pro, Poppins |\n240: | N/A | H1 Size | 48px (hero sections only) |\n241: | N/A | H2 Size | 36px (page titles) |\n242: | N/A | H3 Size | 24px (section headings) |\n243: | N/A | H4 Size | 20px (card titles) |\n244: | N/A | Body Size | 16px (main content) |\n245: | N/A | Small Size | 14px (metadata, labels) |\n246: | N/A | Caption Size | 12px (fine print) |\n247: \n248: **Font Weights:**\n249: - 400 (regular) - Body text\n250: - 500 (medium) - Emphasis\n251: - 600 (semibold) - Headings, buttons\n252: - 700 (bold) - H1, H2, important headings\n253: \n254: **Template:**\n255: ```\n256: ### Typography\n257: - Font: [FONT_FAMILY from PRD or Inter/SF Pro]\n258: - H1: 48px (hero only), H2: 36px, H3: 24px, H4: 20px\n259: - Body: 16px, Small: 14px, Caption: 12px\n260: - Weights: 400 (regular), 500 (medium), 600 (semibold), 700 (bold)\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ### 3.3 Spacing System\n264: \n265: **Always use a grid system:**\n266: \n267: | Spacing Type | Value | Usage |\n268: |--------------|-------|-------|\n269: | Base Unit | 4px or 8px | Grid system foundation |\n270: | Card Padding | 20px or 24px | Inside cards/containers |\n271: | Section Padding | 32px or 40px | Between major sections |\n272: | Between Cards | 16px or 24px | Gap in grids/lists |\n273: | Input Height | 40px or 48px | Form inputs |\n274: | Button Height | 40px or 48px | Buttons |\n275: \n276: **Template:**\n277: ```\n278: ### Spacing\n279: - Base: [4px or 8px] grid\n280: - Card padding: [20px or 24px]\n281: - Section padding: [32px or 40px]\n282: - Between cards: [16px or 24px]\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ### 3.4 Component Specifications\n286: \n287: **From PRD features, identify needed components:**\n288: \n289: | PRD Feature | Component Needed | Standard Specs |\n290: |-------------|-----------------|----------------|\n291: | Login/Signup forms | Input fields | Height: 48px, Radius: 6px |\n292: | Submit buttons | Primary button | Height: 48px, Radius: 6px |\n293: | Cards/Lists | Card component | Padding: 20px, Radius: 12px |\n294: | Voting | Upvote button | Custom size based on prominence |\n295: | Images | Image container | Aspect ratio: 16:9 or 1:1 |\n296: | Icons | Icon size | 16px (inline), 24px (buttons), 32px (features) |\n297: \n298: **Template:**\n299: ```\n300: ### Key Components\n301: \n302: **[Component Name from PRD feature]:**\n303: - [Dimension 1]: [Value]\n304: - [Dimension 2]: [Value]\n305: - [Special feature]: [Description]\n306: - [States]: [Default, Hover, Active]\n307: \n308: **[Component Name 2]:**\n309: - ...\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## PHASE 3.5: VARIATION ARCHETYPE APPLICATION (Differentiating 3 DESIGN_SYSTEMs)\n315: \n316: > **This section MUST be followed when generating 3 DESIGN_SYSTEM variants.**\n317: > **Purpose:** Enforce that each variation has a visually completely different identity.\n318: \n319: ### Core Principles\n320: \n321: The PRD's design tokens (colors, fonts, icons) are a **functional foundation**.\n322: Each DESIGN_SYSTEM **freely reinterprets** these tokens to match the selected archetype.\n323: \n324: **NEVER do this:**\n325: - ❌ Apply the PRD background color (e.g., #F8FAFC) identically across all 3 variations\n326: - ❌ Use the PRD primary color the same way in all 3 (e.g., all solid buttons)\n327: - ❌ Only vary spacing/corners while keeping color/theme identical\n328: \n329: **ALWAYS do this:**\n330: - ✅ Apply a **different background color theme** to each variation (dark vs cream vs white, etc.)\n331: - ✅ **Interpret PRD primary color differently** (gradient glow vs pastel+accent colors vs sparse accent)\n332: - ✅ Apply shadows/borders/corners/typography weights **differently per archetype**\n333: \n334: ### PRD Token Reinterpretation Table (Examples per Archetype)\n335: \n336: This table is an **example**. Adapt appropriately based on the actual archetype combination.\n337: \n338: | PRD Token | Dark Vibrant Reinterpretation | Warm Playful Reinterpretation | Editorial Minimal Reinterpretation |\n339: |-----------|------------------------------|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------|\n340: | Primary color | → Gradient (primary→purple→blue) + glow shadow | → Solid primary + 4 accent colors (coral, teal, amber, lavender) | → Use Primary for CTA/active only, 95% grayscale otherwise |\n341: | Background | → #0B0F1A (deep navy dark) | → #FFFBF5 (warm cream) | → #FFFFFF (pure white) |\n342: | Card background | → rgba(255,255,255,0.05) + backdrop-blur (glass) | → #FFFFFF solid + warm shadow | → #FFFFFF + 0.5px hairline border only |\n343: | Sidebar | → Pure dark + gradient accent on active | → Warm dark purple (#1A1625) + colored icons | → Light sidebar (#F8FAFC) + 2px left border active |\n344: | Status Open | → #FF4757 neon + glow box-shadow | → #FEE2E2 bg + #DC2626 text (pastel pill) | → 6px red dot only, no text label |\n345: | Status In Progress | → #FFB74D neon + glow | → #FEF3C7 bg + #D97706 text | → 6px amber dot only |\n346: | Status Resolved | → #4ADE80 neon + glow | → #D1FAE5 bg + #059669 text | → 6px green dot only |\n347: | Border | → rgba(255,255,255,0.08) transparent | → #F0E7DB warm tone | → #F3F4F6 hairline 0.5px |\n348: | Shadow | → 0 0 20px rgba(primary,0.3) glow | → 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.04) warm | → None (no shadows) |\n349: | Corner radius | → 12-16px (rounded-xl) | → 16-20px + pill buttons (rounded-2xl/full) | → 0-6px max (rounded-md) |\n350: | Heading weight | → 700 bold + tight tracking | → 600 semibold + friendly | → 300 light + editorial size (up to 4.5rem) |\n351: | Button style | → Gradient bg + glow hover | → Pill shape + lift hover | → Minimal border + subtle fill hover |\n352: \n353: ### Differentiation Verification Checklist\n354: \n355: After generating 3 DESIGN_SYSTEMs, compare the 7 items below. **5 or more must differ to pass:**\n356: \n357: | # | Item | A | B | C | Different? |\n358: |---|------|---|---|---|------------|\n359: | 1 | Background color theme | (dark/light/white/cream/gradient) | | | □ |\n360: | 2 | Shadow style | (glow/soft/none/hard/glass) | | | □ |\n361: | 3 | Border treatment | (transparent/warm/hairline/solid) | | | □ |\n362: | 4 | Corner radius | (3xl/2xl/xl/lg/md/0) | | | □ |\n363: | 5 | Typography weight | (700/600/500/400/300) | | | □ |\n364: | 6 | Status color expression | (neon/pastel/dot/solid/badge) | | | □ |\n365: | 7 | Sidebar theme | (dark/warm-dark/light/gradient/none) | | | □ |\n366: \n367: **Pass:** 5/7 or more → proceed\n368: **Fail:** swap archetypes and regenerate\n369: \n370: ---\n371: \n372: ## PHASE 4: CONVERT PAGES TO DESIGN BRIEFS\n373: \n374: ### 4.1 Extract All Pages from PRD\n375: \n376: **From PRD's \"Page Breakdown\" or feature sections:**\n377: \n378: | PRD Section | Page Number | Page Name | Category |\n379: |-------------|-------------|-----------|----------|\n380: | Common/Auth | 1, 2, 3, 4 | Login, Signup, Forgot PW | auth |\n381: | Public | 1, 5, 6 | Landing, About, Browse (Guest) | public |\n382: | User Features | 7, 8, 9... | Dashboard, Profile, Settings | user |\n383: | Admin Dashboard | 20, 21, 22... | Admin Home, Queue, Reports | admin |\n384: \n385: ### 4.2 Convert PRD Page Specs to Design Brief\n386: \n387: **For each page in PRD, create design brief:**\n388: \n389: | PRD Element | Design Guide Format |\n390: |-------------|-------------------|\n391: | Page Name | **PAGE [N]: [Name]** |\n392: | Feature description | Brief one-line description |\n393: | Components listed | Section breakdown with components |\n394: | User actions | Implied in layout description |\n395: \n396: **Conversion Pattern:**\n397: \n398: **PRD Format:**\n399: ```\n400: #### 3.1 Login Page\n401: \n402: **Input:**\n403: - Email Address (required)\n404: - Password (required, show/hide toggle)\n405: \n406: **Next Action:**\n407: - Login button\n408: - \"Forgot Password?\" link\n409: - Social login (Google, Apple)\n410: \n411: **Rules:**\n412: - Email validation\n413: - Password minimum 8 characters\n414: ```\n415: \n416: **Design Guide Format:**\n417: ```\n418: **PAGE 2: Login**\n419: Split screen 40/60: Left (brand gradient) | Right (form: email, password, social buttons)\n420: - Email input (48px, mail icon)\n421: - Password input (48px, lock icon, eye toggle)\n422: - Login button (primary, full-width)\n423: - Forgot password link\n424: - Social buttons: Google, Apple\n425: ```\n426: \n427: **Shorthand Template for Pages:**\n428: ```\n429: **PAGE [N]: [Name]**\n430: [Layout type]: [Section 1] | [Section 2] | [Section 3]\n431: - [Key element 1]\n432: - [Key element 2]\n433: - [Key element 3]\n434: ```\n435: \n436: ### 4.3 Common Layout Patterns\n437: \n438: **Recognize these patterns from PRD:**\n439: \n440: | PRD Description | Layout Pattern | Design Brief Format |\n441: |----------------|---------------|-------------------|\n442: | \"Login/Signup form\" | Split screen auth | \"Split screen 40/60: Left (branding) \\| Right (form)\" |\n443: | \"List of items\", \"Feed\" | Vertical scroll list | \"List/Grid view: Cards with [elements]\" |\n444: | \"Dashboard\" | Sidebar + main content | \"Sidebar nav (200px) \\| Stats cards \\| Activity feed\" |\n445: | \"Detail page\" | Two column | \"Two columns 70/30: Left (content) \\| Right (sidebar)\" |\n446: | \"Form submission\" | Multi-step or single page | \"Multi-step progress bar \\| Sections: [list]\" OR \"Single form: [fields]\" |\n447: | \"Table/List management\" | Table with filters | \"Filter tabs \\| Sortable table \\| Action buttons\" |\n448: | \"Modal/Popup\" | Overlay | \"Modal: [trigger] → [content] → [actions]\" |\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ## PHASE 5: CREATE COMPONENT PATTERNS\n453: \n454: ### 5.1 Identify Reusable Components\n455: \n456: **From PRD, look for repeated elements:**\n457: \n458: | PRD Pattern | Component to Define | Specs to Include |\n459: |-------------|-------------------|-----------------|\n460: | \"Idea card\", \"Post card\", \"Product card\" | Card component | Width, padding, elements, hover state |\n461: | \"Upvote\", \"Like\", \"Vote\" | Vote button | Size, icon, count display |\n462: | \"Comment\", \"Reply\" | Comment thread | Nesting, indentation, avatar size |\n463: | \"Stats\", \"Metrics\", \"Count\" | Stats card | Layout, icon size, number size |\n464: | \"Form\" appears multiple times | Form pattern | Input height, spacing, validation |\n465: \n466: ### 5.2 Component Pattern Template\n467: \n468: **For each reusable component:**\n469: \n470: ```\n471: **[Component Name] ([Style reference]):**\n472: - [Dimension 1]: [Value]\n473: - [Dimension 2]: [Value]\n474: - Elements: [List of sub-elements with sizes]\n475: - States: [Hover, active, disabled, etc.]\n476: - Usage: [Where it's used]\n477: ```\n478: \n479: **Example:**\n480: ```\n481: **Idea Card (Reusable):**\n482: - Width: 280px\n483: - Padding: 20px\n484: - Border radius: 12px\n485: - Shadow on hover\n486: - Elements: Avatar(48px), Title, Tagline, Thumbnail, Tags, Metrics\n487: - Usage: Browse page, Featured section, Saved ideas\n488: ```\n489: \n490: ### 5.3 Add ASCII Diagrams (Optional but Helpful)\n491: \n492: **Create simple visual representations:**\n493: \n494: ```\n495: **[Component Name]:**\n496: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n497: │ [Element 1]  [Element 2]    │\n498: │ [Element 3]                 │\n499: │ [Element 4 with sizing]     │\n500: └─────────────────────────────┘\n501: ```\n502: \n503: ---\n504: \n505: ## PHASE 6: CREATE CRITICAL DESIGN RULES\n506: \n507: ### 6.1 Extract Rules from PRD Features\n508: \n509: **Look for these in PRD:**\n510: \n511: | PRD Content | Design Rule |\n512: |-------------|------------|\n513: | \"18+ platform\", \"Age verification\" | \"Show age notice on landing, signup, footer\" |\n514: | \"Upvoting is core feature\" | \"Make upvote button HUGE and prominent\" |\n515: | \"Professional platform\" | \"Professional typography, generous whitespace\" |\n516: | \"Fast user experience\" | \"Loading states on all async actions\" |\n517: | Specific status (Original, Similar, Duplicate) | \"Color-coded status badges: Green, Orange, Red\" |\n518: | \"Mobile app\" | \"Mobile-first design, thumb-friendly tap targets\" |\n519: \n520: ### 6.2 Add Universal Design Principles\n521: \n522: **Always include:**\n523: \n524: 1. **Whitespace** - Don't cramp, be generous\n525: 2. **One Primary Action** - Per page (reduces cognitive load)\n526: 3. **Consistent Components** - Reuse design system\n527: 4. **Hover States** - Feedback on interactive elements\n528: 5. **Loading States** - For all async operations\n529: 6. **Empty States** - For zero-data scenarios\n530: 7. **Error States** - Clear, helpful error messages\n531: 8. **Accessibility** - 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum\n532: 9. **Responsive** - Mobile/tablet/desktop considerations\n533: 10. **Performance** - Optimize images, lazy load\n534: \n535: ### 6.3 Template\n536: \n537: ```\n538: ## Critical Design Rules\n539: \n540: 1. **[Rule from PRD feature]** - [Specific guideline]\n541: 2. **[Universal principle]** - [Application]\n542: 3. **[Platform-specific requirement]** - [Implementation]\n543: ...\n544: 10. **[Performance/accessibility rule]** - [Standard]\n545: ```\n546: \n547: ---\n548: \n549: ## PHASE 7: CREATE DELIVERABLES PLAN\n550: \n551: ### 7.1 Timeline from PRD\n552: \n553: **Extract timeline and create phases:**\n554: \n555: | PRD Timeline | Design Phases | Days Allocated |\n556: |-------------|--------------|----------------|\n557: | 1 week | Research & Wireframes | 1-2 days |\n558: | 2 weeks | Wireframes, Mockups | 3-5 days |\n559: | 4 weeks | Wireframes, Mockups, System, Handoff | 5 days |\n560: | 2 months | Full design cycle with iterations | 2-3 weeks |\n561: \n562: ### 7.2 Deliverables Checklist Template\n563: \n564: **Adapt based on timeline:**\n565: \n566: ```\n567: ## Deliverables Checklist\n568: \n569: **Day 1-2: Research & Wireframes**\n570: - [ ] Study inspiration sites ([list from Design Philosophy])\n571: - [ ] Collect reference images\n572: - [ ] Low-fidelity wireframes (all [TOTAL_PAGES] pages)\n573: \n574: **Day 3-[N]: High-Fidelity Mockups**\n575: - [ ] High-fidelity mockups ([N] key pages):\n576:   - [Page 1 from PRD]\n577:   - [Page 2]\n578:   - [Page 3]\n579:   - ...\n580: - [ ] Remaining pages\n581: \n582: **Day [N+1]-[N+2]: Design System & Components**\n583: - [ ] Design system (colors, typography, spacing)\n584: - [ ] Component library creation\n585: - [ ] Interactive prototype (key flows)\n586: \n587: **Day [N+3]-[Final]: Finalization**\n588: - [ ] Dark mode variants (if applicable)\n589: - [ ] Responsive designs (mobile, tablet)\n590: - [ ] Design QA, final polish\n591: - [ ] Handoff documentation\n592: \n593: **Final Delivery:**\n594: - [ ] Figma file with all pages\n595: - [ ] Component library (organized, documented)\n596: - [ ] Design system guide\n597: - [ ] Icon set (SVG exports)\n598: - [ ] Image assets (optimized)\n599: - [ ] Interactive prototype link\n600: - [ ] Developer handoff notes\n601: ```\n602: \n603: ### 7.3 Priority Order\n604: \n605: **From PRD, determine page priority:**\n606: \n607: **Criteria:**\n608: - Landing page = Highest (first impression)\n609: - Auth pages = High (entry point)\n610: - Core features = High (main value)\n611: - Admin pages = Medium (internal tool)\n612: - Legal/Settings = Low (necessary but not core)\n613: \n614: **Template:**\n615: ```\n616: **Priority Order:**\n617: 1. [Landing/Homepage] (first impression)\n618: 2. [Auth pages] (entry point)\n619: 3. [Core feature pages] (main value)\n620: 4. [Dashboard] (regular use)\n621: 5. [Admin pages] (internal)\n622: 6. [Settings/Legal] (necessary)\n623: ```\n624: \n625: ---\n626: \n627: ## COMPLETE DESIGN GUIDE TEMPLATE\n628: \n629: **Use this template structure:**\n630: \n631: ```markdown\n632: # [PROJECT_NAME] - Design Guide for [DESIGNER_NAME]\n633: \n634: **Project:** [PROJECT_NAME] [VERSION]\n635: **Designer:** [DESIGNER_NAME]\n636: **Timeline:** [TIMELINE]\n637: \n638: ---\n639: \n640: ## Design Philosophy\n641: \n642: **Core Inspiration (Must Study):**\n643: 1. **[Reference App 1]** - [Feature to study]\n644: 2. **[Reference App 2]** - [Feature to study]\n645: 3. **[Reference App 3]** - [Feature to study]\n646: 4. **[Reference App 4]** - [Feature to study]\n647: \n648: **The [Number] Pillars:**\n649: - [Feature Area 1] = [Reference] ([pattern])\n650: - [Feature Area 2] = [Reference] ([pattern])\n651: - [Feature Area 3] = [Reference] ([pattern])\n652: \n653: ---\n654: \n655: ## Page Count: [TOTAL_PAGES] Total Pages\n656: \n657: **[User Type 1] ([N] pages):**\n658: [Page numbers]: [Page names]\n659: \n660: **[User Type 2] ([N] pages):**\n661: [Page numbers]: [Page names]\n662: \n663: **[User Type 3] ([N] pages):**\n664: [Page numbers]: [Page names]\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## Design System Quick Reference\n669: \n670: ### Colors\n671: - Primary [Name]: [HEX] ([Usage])\n672: - Success [Name]: [HEX] ([Usage])\n673: - Warning [Name]: [HEX] ([Usage])\n674: - Error [Name]: [HEX] ([Usage])\n675: - Grays: 50-900 scale\n676: \n677: ### Typography\n678: - Font: [FONT_FAMILY]\n679: - H1: [SIZE]px (hero only), H2: [SIZE]px, H3: [SIZE]px, H4: [SIZE]px\n680: - Body: [SIZE]px, Small: [SIZE]px, Caption: [SIZE]px\n681: - Weights: 400 (regular), 500 (medium), 600 (semibold), 700 (bold)\n682: \n683: ### Spacing\n684: - Base: [BASE_UNIT] grid\n685: - Card padding: [VALUE]\n686: - Section padding: [VALUE]\n687: - Between cards: [VALUE]\n688: \n689: ### Key Components\n690: \n691: **[Component 1 Name]:**\n692: - [Spec 1]: [Value]\n693: - [Spec 2]: [Value]\n694: - [Usage]: [Where used]\n695: \n696: **[Component 2 Name]:**\n697: - [Spec 1]: [Value]\n698: - [Spec 2]: [Value]\n699: \n700: ---\n701: \n702: ## Page-by-Page Design Brief\n703: \n704: ### [USER_TYPE_1] PAGES\n705: \n706: **PAGE 1: [Page Name]**\n707: [Layout description]: [Section 1] | [Section 2] | [Section 3]\n708: - [Key element 1]\n709: - [Key element 2]\n710: - [Key element 3]\n711: \n712: **PAGE 2: [Page Name]**\n713: [Layout description]\n714: - [Elements]\n715: \n716: ### [USER_TYPE_2] PAGES\n717: \n718: **PAGE [N]: [Page Name]**\n719: [Layout description]\n720: - [Elements]\n721: \n722: ### [USER_TYPE_3] PAGES\n723: \n724: **PAGE [N]: [Page Name]**\n725: [Layout description]\n726: - [Elements]\n727: \n728: ---\n729: \n730: ## Critical Design Rules\n731: \n732: 1. **[Rule 1]** - [Description]\n733: 2. **[Rule 2]** - [Description]\n734: 3. **[Rule 3]** - [Description]\n735: ...\n736: 10. **[Rule 10]** - [Description]\n737: \n738: ---\n739: \n740: ## Component Patterns\n741: \n742: ### [Component 1] (Reusable)\n743: ```\n744: [ASCII diagram if helpful]\n745: ```\n746: - [Specs]\n747: - [Elements]\n748: - [Usage]\n749: \n750: ### [Component 2]\n751: ```\n752: [ASCII diagram if helpful]\n753: ```\n754: - [Specs]\n755: \n756: ---\n757: \n758: ## Deliverables Checklist\n759: \n760: **Day 1-2:**\n761: - [ ] [Tasks]\n762: \n763: **Day 3-[N]:**\n764: - [ ] [Tasks]\n765: \n766: **Day [N+1]:**\n767: - [ ] [Tasks]\n768: \n769: **Final Delivery:**\n770: - [ ] Figma file\n771: - [ ] Component library\n772: - [ ] Design system guide\n773: - [ ] Assets\n774: - [ ] Prototype\n775: - [ ] Handoff docs\n776: \n777: ---\n778: \n779: ## Design Tips\n780: \n781: 1. **Consistency First** - Use design system components everywhere\n782: 2. **Accessibility** - 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum\n783: 3. **Performance** - Optimize images, use SVG icons\n784: 4. **Responsive** - [Desktop/Mobile]-first approach\n785: 5. **States** - Loading, empty, error for everything\n786: 6. **Real Content** - Use realistic text, not Lorem Ipsum\n787: 7. **Whitespace** - Generous spacing\n788: 8. **Hierarchy** - Clear visual importance\n789: 9. **Feedback** - User knows what's happening\n790: 10. **Polish** - Subtle animations, consistent shadows\n791: \n792: ---\n793: \n794: ## Success Criteria\n795: \n796: Your design succeeds if:\n797: - ✅ [Feature 1] looks like [Reference App] ([pattern])\n798: - ✅ [Feature 2] feels [adjective]\n799: - ✅ Users can [core action] easily\n800: - ✅ Platform feels [brand adjective - professional/playful/trustworthy]\n801: - ✅ All [TOTAL_PAGES] pages designed\n802: - ✅ Component library complete\n803: - ✅ Responsive at all breakpoints\n804: \n805: ---\n806: \n807: **Priority Order:**\n808: 1. [Page 1] (reason)\n809: 2. [Page 2] (reason)\n810: 3. [Page 3] (reason)\n811: 4. [Page 4] (reason)\n812: 5. [Page 5] (reason)\n813: \n814: Good luck! 🎨🚀\n815: ```\n816: \n817: ---\n818: \n819: ## CONVERSION EXAMPLES\n820: \n821: ### Example 1: Login Page\n822: \n823: **PRD Input:**\n824: ```\n825: #### 2.1 Login Page\n826: \n827: **Input:**\n828: - Email Address (required)\n829: - Password (required)\n830: - Show/hide password toggle\n831: \n832: **Actions:**\n833: - Login button (primary)\n834: - \"Forgot Password?\" link\n835: - Social login: Google, Apple\n836: \n837: **Next:**\n838: - Success → Dashboard\n839: - Error → Show message\n840: ```\n841: \n842: **Design Guide Output:**\n843: ```\n844: **PAGE 2: Login**\n845: Split screen 40/60: Left (brand gradient) | Right (form: email, password, social buttons)\n846: \n847: Elements:\n848: - Email input (48px height, mail icon)\n849: - Password input (48px height, lock icon, eye toggle)\n850: - Login button (primary, full-width, 48px)\n851: - \"Forgot Password?\" link (below form)\n852: - Divider: \"Or continue with\"\n853: - Social buttons: Google (white bg), Apple (black bg)\n854: ```\n855: \n856: ### Example 2: Dashboard\n857: \n858: **PRD Input:**\n859: ```\n860: #### 5.1 Admin Dashboard\n861: \n862: **Sidebar Navigation:**\n863: 1. Overview\n864: 2. Pending Approvals\n865: 3. Reports\n866: 4. Settings\n867: \n868: **Main Content:**\n869: - Stats cards (4 metrics)\n870: - Recent activity feed\n871: - Quick actions\n872: ```\n873: \n874: **Design Guide Output:**\n875: ```\n876: **PAGE 20: Admin Home**\n877: Sidebar nav (200px, collapsible) | Stats cards (4 across) | Activity feed | Quick actions\n878: \n879: Layout:\n880: - Sidebar: Navigation items, icons 20px, active state with primary color\n881: - Stats cards: Icon 32px, metric 32px bold, label 14px gray\n882: - Activity feed: Timeline style, avatar 32px, timestamp\n883: - Quick actions: Button row at top\n884: ```\n885: \n886: ### Example 3: Form Submission\n887: \n888: **PRD Input:**\n889: ```\n890: #### 3.2 Submit Idea\n891: \n892: **Step 1: Basic Info**\n893: - Project Name (max 100 chars)\n894: - Tagline (max 150 chars)\n895: - Category (dropdown)\n896: \n897: **Step 2: Story**\n898: - Rich text editor (max 5000 chars)\n899: \n900: **Step 3: SWOT Analysis**\n901: - Strengths, Weaknesses, Opportunities, Threats\n902: \n903: **Step 4: Media**\n904: - Upload images (max 5)\n905: - Upload video OR YouTube link\n906: ```\n907: \n908: **Design Guide Output:**\n909: ```\n910: **PAGE 8: Submit Idea**\n911: Multi-step progress bar | Sections: Basic Info | Story (rich editor) | SWOT (2x2 grid) | Media upload | Actions\n912: \n913: Progress bar: 5 steps, show completion, click to navigate completed steps\n914: - Step 1: Project name input, tagline input, category dropdown\n915: - Step 2: Rich text editor (400px height, char counter)\n916: - Step 3: SWOT grid (2x2, equal quadrants, textarea each)\n917: - Step 4: Image uploader (drag-drop, preview grid), video upload/URL\n918: - Actions: Back, Next/Submit buttons (bottom, full-width on mobile)\n919: ```\n920: \n921: ---\n922: \n923: ## QUICK REFERENCE CHECKLIST\n924: \n925: **Before starting conversion:**\n926: - [ ] PRD read completely\n927: - [ ] Project name, timeline, designer extracted\n928: - [ ] All pages counted\n929: - [ ] User types identified\n930: \n931: **Phase 1 - Basic Info:**\n932: - [ ] Project metadata extracted\n933: - [ ] Page count calculated\n934: - [ ] User types listed\n935: \n936: **Phase 2 - Design Philosophy:**\n937: - [ ] Reference apps identified from features\n938: - [ ] Design pillars created (3-4)\n939: - [ ] Inspiration mapped to features\n940: \n941: **Phase 3 - Design System:**\n942: - [ ] Colors defined (primary, success, warning, error + neutrals)\n943: - [ ] Typography specified (font, sizes, weights)\n944: - [ ] Spacing system created (base unit, padding, gaps)\n945: - [ ] Component specs started\n946: \n947: **Phase 4 - Page Conversion:**\n948: - [ ] All pages from PRD listed\n949: - [ ] Each page converted to shorthand design brief\n950: - [ ] Layout patterns identified\n951: - [ ] Key elements listed\n952: \n953: **Phase 5 - Component Patterns:**\n954: - [ ] Reusable components identified\n955: - [ ] Specs for each component\n956: - [ ] ASCII diagrams (optional)\n957: - [ ] Usage notes\n958: \n959: **Phase 6 - Design Rules:**\n960: - [ ] PRD-specific rules extracted\n961: - [ ] Universal principles added\n962: - [ ] Platform requirements noted\n963: \n964: **Phase 7 - Deliverables:**\n965: - [ ] Timeline converted to phases\n966: - [ ] Checklist created\n967: - [ ] Priority order defined\n968: - [ ] Success criteria listed\n969: \n970: **Final Review:**\n971: - [ ] All [PLACEHOLDERS] filled\n972: - [ ] Page count matches PRD\n973: - [ ] Design philosophy makes sense\n974: - [ ] Component patterns are reusable\n975: - [ ] Design Guide is actionable for designer\n976: \n977: ---\n978: \n979: ## OUTPUT FILE\n980: \n981: **Save as:**\n982: - **Filename:** `[ProjectName]_DesignGuide_[YYMMDD].md`\n983: - **Location:** `.claude-project/design/` or project root\n984: - **Format:** Markdown (.md)\n985: \n986: **Share with:**\n987: - Designer (primary recipient)\n988: - Developer (for context)\n989: - Project Manager (for timeline)\n990: \n991: ---\n992: \n993: **Template Version:** 1.0\n994: **Created:** January 15, 2026\n995: **Purpose:** Convert any PRD to Design Guide\n996: **Reusable:** Yes, for all projects\n\n(End of file - total 996 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: prd-to-design-guide\ndescription: Convert PRD to Design Guide (used in both Path A automated and Path B external designer)\n---\n\n# PRD to Design Guide - Generic Template for All Projects\n\nThis is a **comprehensive reusable template** for converting any Product Requirements Document (PRD) into a Design Guide. Used in the fullstack pipeline Phase 3 (Design) as the first sub-phase for both Path A (Full AI Generation) and Path B (External Designer). The Design Guide serves as a human-readable review checkpoint before HTML generation.\n\n---\n\n## HOW TO USE THIS TEMPLATE\n\n1. **Read your PRD thoroughly**\n2. **Extract information using the tables below**\n3. **Fill in the Design Guide template** with extracted data\n4. **Follow the conversion patterns** for each section\n5. **Output a complete Design Guide** ready for your designer\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/skills/design/prd-to-design-guide/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1779179351996,"end":1779179352282}},"id":"prt_e3f5a691b001vSaUb3GltiHt11","sessionID":"ses_1c0a5da53ffeUiGM7BSSxJYePS","messageID":"msg_e3f5a2943001MXyk7M2U4BZZZz"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779179571113,"sessionID":"ses_1c0a5da53ffeUiGM7BSSxJYePS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_00_kXh77gOHtpehYQ3xXA7f5962","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore nestfind design docs","prompt":"Explore the nestfind project design directory. I need to understand:\n\n1. What files exist under .claude-project/nestfind/design/ and .claude-project/nestfind/docs/\n2. Read the full content of .claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md\n3. Read .claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md\n4. Look for any existing DESIGN_SYSTEM or design guide files\n5. Look for any PRD files under .claude-project/nestfind/\n6. Check if a .claude-project/nestfind/design/variations/ directory exists\n\nReturn ALL file contents and directory listings found.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_1c0a59862ffeIhHrEDcYKr84Qh (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a complete report of all findings across the nestfind project design directory.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Directory: `.claude-project/nestfind/design/` (6 entries)\n\n| File/Dir | Type |\n|-----------|------|\n| `DESIGN_SYSTEM_A.md` | file |\n| `DESIGN_SYSTEM_B.md` | file |\n| `DESIGN_SYSTEM_C.md` | file |\n| `DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md` | file |\n| `VARIATIONS_INDEX.md` | file |\n| `variations/` | directory (10 entries) |\n\n## 2. Directory: `.claude-project/nestfind/design/variations/` (10 entries)\n\n| File | Page Type | Archetype |\n|------|-----------|-----------|\n| `A-01-landing.html` | Landing | Dark Tech (Linear) |\n| `A-02-dashboard.html` | Dashboard | Dark Tech (Linear) |\n| `A-03-detail.html` | Property Detail | Dark Tech (Linear) |\n| `B-01-landing.html` | Landing | Warm Homely (Notion) |\n| `B-02-dashboard.html` | Dashboard | Warm Homely (Notion) |\n| `B-03-detail.html` | Property Detail | Warm Homely (Notion) |\n| `C-01-landing.html` | Landing | Clean Editorial (Apple) |\n| `C-02-dashboard.html` | Dashboard | Clean Editorial (Apple) |\n| `C-03-detail.html` | Property Detail | Clean Editorial (Apple) |\n| `showcase-ALL.html` | Side-by-side iframe grid of all 9 variants | N/A |\n\n## 3. Directory: `.claude-project/nestfind/docs/` (3 entries)\n\n| File | Lines | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| `PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md` | 322 | PRD — core project info, features, roles, architecture, glossary |\n| `PROJECT_API.md` | 1,621 | Full API contract with 47 endpoints across 7 resource groups |\n| `PROJECT_DATABASE.md` | 394 | 8 entities, 4 enums, ER diagram, FK summary |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Full Content of `DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md`\n\n**Path:** `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md`\n**Lines:** 393\n\nThis is the competitive domain research document generated during Phase 2.5. Key sections:\n\n- **Industry:** Real Estate / Rental Property Listings (PropTech subset). Market context covers Zillow, Apartments.com, Realtor.com dominance.\n- **5 Competitors Analyzed:**\n  1. Zillow Rentals — landing, search/listing, detail, renter hub patterns\n  2. Apartments.com — filter-heavy, rating stars, admin manager dashboard\n  3. Airbnb — category chips, immersive photo-first, sticky booking sidebar\n  4. Rentable (rentable.co) — verified listings focus, social proof sections, city grids\n  5. HotPads — map-centric, polygon search, color-coded price pins\n- **7 Reference UI Patterns:** Property Search Card, Search Filter Panel, Photo Gallery, Map Integration, Favorites/Saved, Inquiry/Contact Form, Admin Dashboard\n- **Page-type Conventions:** Landing (11 standard sections), Renter Dashboard (5 elements), Admin Dashboard (10 elements), Property Detail (10 sections), Auth Pages (7 patterns)\n- **PRD Reference Analysis:** Maps every PRD feature to a dominant UI pattern from competitors\n- **Design Gap Analysis:** Opportunities — ad-free, streamlined inquiry, quick favorites, simple admin, mobile-first\n- **NestFind Differentiators:** 5 key design principles to emphasize\n\n---\n\n## 5. Full Content of `PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md`\n\n**Path:** `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md`\n**Lines:** 322\n\nThis is the canonical PRD document. Key sections:\n\n- **Application Purpose:** Streamlined rental property listing platform connecting renters with properties. Two user groups: Renters and Admins.\n- **Tech Stack:** NestJS 11 + TypeScript 5.7+, React 19 + React Router 7 (framework mode), PostgreSQL 16, TypeORM 0.3.x, JWT httpOnly cookies, Redux Toolkit, Tailwind CSS 4 + Shadcn/UI, Google Maps API, Docker.\n- **User Roles:** Renter (4 permissions), Admin (4 permissions), Guest (2 permissions)\n- **Auth:** JWT via httpOnly cookies (Access: 1h, Refresh: 7d), RBAC with JwtAuthGuard + RolesGuard\n- **Core Features:**\n  - Common: Auth, Registration, Password Reset\n  - Renter: Property Search, Detail View, Favorites Management, Submit Inquiry\n  - Admin: Dashboard, Property CRUD, Inquiry Management, User Management\n- **20+ Functional Requirements** with FR-IDs across Auth, Search, Details, Inquiries, Admin-Property, Admin-Inquiry, Admin-User\n- **12 Non-Functional Requirements** covering Performance, Security, Reliability, Maintainability, Compatibility\n- **Glossary:** 24 terms defined (BaseEntity, soft delete, RBAC, createAsyncThunk, etc.)\n- **Architecture Overview:** 4-layer backend (Controller -> Service -> Repository -> Entity), frontend patterns, full directory tree\n\n---\n\n## 6. DESIGN_SYSTEM Files (3 Found)\n\nAll three are located in `.claude-project/nestfind/design/`:\n\n### DESIGN_SYSTEM_A.md — \"Dark Vibrant\" (Linear-inspired)\n**167 lines.** Archetype: Dark Tech / Glass Morphism\n- **Background:** `#0B0F1A` dark navy\n- **Primary:** `#4A90D9` with `#4A90D9 → #7C3AED` gradient CTAs\n- **Cards:** Glass morphism — `rgba(255,255,255,0.04)` bg + `backdrop-filter: blur(12px)`\n- **Status Badges:** Neon glow (colored text + matching box-shadow glow)\n- **Sidebar:** `#080B14` dark + gradient left border\n- **Corner Radius:** 12-16px (rounded-xl)\n- **Typography:** 600-700 bold, tight tracking, Inter font\n- **Shadows:** Glow shadows (e.g., `0 0 20px rgba(74,144,217,0.15)` on card hover)\n- **Buttons:** Gradient primary, 48px height, 12px radius, glow on hover\n\n### DESIGN_SYSTEM_B.md — \"Warm Friendly\" (Notion-inspired)\n**170 lines.** Archetype: Warm Playful / Soft Organic\n- **Background:** `#FFFBF5` warm cream\n- **Primary:** `#4A90D9` solid blue + 4 accent colors (coral, teal, amber, lavender)\n- **Cards:** White bg `#FFFFFF`, warm border `#F0E7DB`, 20px radius, soft shadows, lift on hover\n- **Status Badges:** Pastel pills (light colored bg + dark saturated text)\n- **Sidebar:** `#1A1625` warm dark purple, colored dot nav indicators\n- **Corner Radius:** 16-20px + full pill (rounded-2xl/full)\n- **Typography:** 600 semibold, open tracking, SF Pro Display + Inter\n- **Shadows:** Soft warm shadows (`0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.04)`)\n- **Buttons:** Full pill (9999px radius), lift animation on hover\n\n### DESIGN_SYSTEM_C.md — \"Editorial Minimal\" (Apple-inspired)\n**170 lines.** Archetype: Editorial Minimal / Typography-First\n- **Background:** `#FFFFFF` pure white\n- **Primary:** `#4A90D9` used ONLY for CTAs and active states; 95% grayscale\n- **Cards:** White bg, 0.5px hairline `#F3F4F6` border, 4px near-rectangular radius, NO shadows\n- **Status Indicators:** 6px dot only (no text, no backgrounds, tooltip on hover)\n- **Sidebar:** `#F8FAFC` light gray, 2px primary left border for active\n- **Corner Radius:** 0-6px max (rounded-md)\n- **Typography:** 300-400 light weight, editorial scales (H1: 64px light), Inter\n- **Shadows:** None anywhere — whitespace does the work\n- **Buttons:** 44px height, 6px radius, no lift, just bg darkens 5%\n\n---\n\n## 7. PRD Files\n\n**No files named `PRD*.md` or `*PRD*.md` found in `.claude-project/nestfind/`.** However, several PRD-related artifacts exist:\n\n| File | Type | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md` | Markdown | The canonical PRD document (322 lines) |\n| `status/seed.yaml` | YAML | Original seed config that drove PRD generation (71 lines) |\n| `status/.blueprint-prd.json` | JSON | Blueprint tracking for PRD phase — 6 nodes, all PASS, \"completed\" (74 lines) |\n| `status/.gate-proofs/prd.proof` | JSON | Gate proof: 6/6 checks passed, score 1.00 |\n| `agent-logs/generate-prd-2026-05-19T05-22-36-343Z.log` | Log | Agent log from PRD generation (18 turns, $0.079 cost) |\n| `agent-logs/generate-prd-2026-05-19T05-00-14-060Z.log` | Log | Earlier PRD generation attempt |\n\nThe PRD blueprint JSON confirms that `PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md` **is** the artifact produced by the `generate-prd` node.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `.claude-project/nestfind/design/variations/` Directory\n\n**EXISTS.** Located at `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/variations/`\n\nContains **10 HTML files**: 9 individual page variations (3 archetypes x 3 page types) plus 1 showcase grid:\n\n| File | Archetype | Page | Key Features |\n|------|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `A-01-landing.html` | Dark Tech | Landing | Gradient hero, glass cards, neon badges, glow CTA |\n| `A-02-dashboard.html` | Dark Tech | Dashboard | Dark glass sidebar, neon stats, glow status badges |\n| `A-03-detail.html` | Dark Tech | Property Detail | Glass gallery, gradient price, glow inquiry form |\n| `B-01-landing.html` | Warm Homely | Landing | Cream bg, pill search, soft shadows, coral accents |\n| `B-02-dashboard.html` | Warm Homely | Dashboard | Purple sidebar, pastel stat cards, pill statuses |\n| `B-03-detail.html` | Warm Homely | Property Detail | Rounded gallery, warm stats bar, pastel amenity cards |\n| `C-01-landing.html` | Clean Editorial | Landing | Pure white, 64px light hero, hairline borders, minimal cards |\n| `C-02-dashboard.html` | Clean Editorial | Dashboard | Light sidebar, lightwe